    <h1>Using the Google Artefact Repo for images</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 id=3D"UsingtheGoogleArtefactRepoforimages-Why?">Why?</h2>
<p>Well , it best practice to have your Artefacts under strict control. We =
use the <strong>Google Artefact Repo</strong>. It is scanned for malware et=
c. </p>
<p>However, it is most important to control K8s versioning very tightly sin=
ce an unintended upgrade WILL cause failures in any cluster - they are very=
 difficult to even find. Many of the public Repos only publish =E2=80=9Clat=
est=E2=80=9D and that may cause an unintended upgrade. </p>
<p>When using a GKE or GCP-DIY cluster the Artefacts are native and seen au=
tomatically. When Using other Cloud DIY or BareMetal clusters you need to a=
uthenticate with our <strong>Google Artefact Repo</strong>.</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://blog.container-solutions.com/using-google-container-r=
egistry-with-kubernetes" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">The websi=
te on Google Artefact usage</a>. This is the resource to see.</p>
<h2 id=3D"UsingtheGoogleArtefactRepoforimages-Therestofthisdocumentiswhatwe=
didforthenginxdeploymentonBareMetal.">The rest of this document is what we =
did for the nginx deployment on BareMetal.</h2>
<p>This is a manual process and we are now going to automate it. When creat=
ing new environments, this is the manual method.</p>
<h3 id=3D"UsingtheGoogleArtefactRepoforimages-ManualMethod:">Manual Method:=
</h3>
<p>Obtain the <strong>json</strong> formatted script from the BitBucket Rep=
o under the <strong>/gitops/ansible/k8_configurations/ConfigFiles</strong> =
directory. It kooks like this:</p>
<p>The file name is : <code>nsight-version-2-4f363527c359.json</code> </p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
  "type": "service_account",
  "project_id": "insight-version-2",
  "private_key_id": "4f363527c359c5e08daf51e64325f018d272dad9",
  "private_key": "-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nMIIExxxxxxxxxx\n-----END PRI=
VATE KEY-----\n",
  "client_email": "imagepull-service-account@insight-version-2.iam.gservice=
account.com",
  "client_id": "yyyyyyy",
  "auth_uri": "https://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/auth",
  "token_uri": "https://oauth2.googleapis.com/token",
  "auth_provider_x509_cert_url": "https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v1/cert=
s",
  "client_x509_cert_url": "https://www.googleapis.com/robot/v1/metadata/x50=
9/imagepull-service-account%40insight-version-2.iam.gserviceaccount.com"
}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>Download the file (ssh copy) to you directory on the appropriate bastion=
s server.</p>
<p>Execute these commands:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">-&gt; k=
ubectl create secret docker-registry gcr-json-key --docker-server=3Deurope-=
west4-docker.pkg.dev --docker-username=3D_json_key --docker-password=3D"$(c=
at insight-version-2-4f363527c359.json)" --docker-email=3Dwillie.spence@pre=
voir.mu -n web
    see this output :: secret/gcr-json-key created
##Then add the secret to the default service account:
-&gt;kubectl patch serviceaccount default -p '{=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=
=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B"imagePullSecrets": [{=E2=80=
=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B"name": "=
gcr-json-key"}=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=
=8B=E2=80=8B]}=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=
=8B=E2=80=8B'
  see this output ::serviceaccount/default patched (no change)</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><code>This means, that for each deployment we need to create the secret =
using that jsonkey so that it's available in all the namespaces.</code></p>
<p>Notes:</p>
<ol>
<li><p>In code line 1 above you will see that the namespace used for nginx =
needs to have that key. (<code>-n web</code>)</p></li>
<li><p>NB: the secret must be in the.. <code>serviceaccount default</code> =
..and the deployment namespace.. <code>-n web</code> ..</p></li>
<li><p>now you refer to that key <code>gcr-json-key</code>=E2=80=A6. in the=
 yaml of the chart .. E.g. for <strong>nginx values .yaml </strong>this is =
the bit that works .</p></li>
<li>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">    ## =
The name of the secret containing docker registry credentials.
    ## Secret must exist in the same namespace as the helm release.
    imagePullSecretName: "gcr-json-key"</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p> </p></li>
<li><p>If you used argoCD - delete the app (with cascade) before redeployin=
g it.</p></li>
<li><p>To delete a Key:</p></li>
</ol>
<p><code>kubectl delete secret gcr-json-key</code></p>
<p></p>
<p>EOF();</p>
